# Persistence

## Plan

- Drizzle schema: canvases, nodes, edges tables
- Neon Postgres connection + migrations
- API routes for all CRUD operations
- Optimistic updates ‚Äî UI updates instantly, API call in background
- Single hardcoded canvas (no auth yet)
- Loading state on initial canvas fetch

## Built

### Stage 2 (2026-03-27)

**Write-on-save flow:**
- Click/long-press creates a temp node (`temp_${Date.now()}`) in local state only ‚Äî no DB write
- Temp metadata (explicitFromId, tempEdgeId) stored in `tempMetaRef`
- `onSave`: if id starts with `temp_`, POSTs to `/api/nodes` with text + position, reconciles temp IDs with real IDs in nodes and edges state
- `onDiscard`: removes temp node/edge from state only ‚Äî no DB call
- `onDelete`: optimistic remove + DELETE API with rollback on failure
- `onNodeMove`: updates state; skips PATCH for temp nodes

**API routes (all wrap DB calls in `withRetry`):**
- `GET/POST /api/canvases` ‚Äî list all / create
- `GET/PATCH/DELETE /api/canvases/[id]` ‚Äî fetch with nodes+edges / rename / delete
- `POST /api/nodes` ‚Äî insert node, auto-nearest edge or explicitFromId
- `PATCH/DELETE /api/nodes/[id]` ‚Äî partial update / delete cascade
- `POST /api/edges` ‚Äî create edge, validates no self-loops
- `DELETE /api/edges/[id]` ‚Äî delete edge

**Ghost node filter:** nearest-node query excludes nodes with no text and no url to prevent ghost nodes poisoning future edge connections.

### Post-Stage 2 Bugfixes (2026-03-28)

- **Ghost edge on discard:** `tempMetaRef.current.set` was inside `setNodes` updater ‚Äî React timing meant it wasn't set when `onDiscard` fired. Fixed by moving ref operations outside the callback using `nodesRef.current`
- **Canvas creation on failed load:** fetch failure was silently clearing localStorage and creating a new canvas, losing the user's canvas ID. Fixed to surface the error and return early

### Session Color Persistence (2026-03-29)
- `color` column added to both `nodes` and `edges` tables (migration `0001_gifted_elektra.sql`)
- `POST /api/nodes` accepts `color` + `edgeColor`, persists to both inserts
- `POST /api/edges` accepts `color`, persists to edge insert

